say something? I feel like
I should be allowed to.

23:54.123 --> 23:55.999
Legally, do I have
to let him talk?

23:56.082 --> 23:57.540
Fine, here.
Here's the mic.

23:57.624 --> 23:58.832
-I'll be quick.
-All right. I'm out.

23:58.916 --> 24:00.582
Hey, Marcia!
Wait up, guys!

24:00.665 --> 24:03.165
I just have to say
Jim Carrey and Adam Sandler

24:03.248 --> 24:05.874
can both be American treasures
and they are.

24:05.957 --> 24:08.707
They've both given so much joy
to so many people,

24:08.791 --> 24:11.041
and, ultimately, isn't
that what it's all about?

24:11.123 --> 24:13.165
And plus, by the way,
Jim's from Canada,

24:13.248 --> 24:15.373
so it's kind of not even
an American treasure
sort of thing, that doesn't--

24:15.457 --> 24:16.916
He's like Mike Myers,
you know-- Oh my!

24:16.999 --> 24:19.582
Mike Myers would've been
so good for this!

24:19.665 --> 24:22.749
I just realized Eddie Murphy
would've won this!

24:22.832 --> 24:26.707
Okay, I'm starting to realize
that this whole exercise is
actually pretty silly.

24:26.791 --> 24:29.916
You know what? I think
I'm gonna devote my time
to the greater good now,

24:29.999 --> 24:32.123
maybe like inter-species rights
with the city,

24:32.207 --> 24:34.248
away from all this glitz
and the glamour.

24:34.332 --> 24:35.874
I think that's
where I'll be happy.

24:35.957 --> 24:37.582
-Sack tap!
-(groans)

24:37.665 --> 24:40.248
Crowd (chanting):
Mike! Mike! Mike! Mike! Mike!

24:40.332 --> 24:41.582
Female:
Woo-hoo!

24:41.665 --> 24:44.582
No, no, no, no!
Why not Jim Carrey?

